description: Pandora A/S designs, manufactures, and markets hand-finished and contemporary jewelry worldwide. The company's jewelry material includes silver and gold; gold and rose gold plated; man-made stones, natural stones, synthetic stones, pearls, and diamonds; as well as enamel, glass, leather, and textile products. Its products primarily include charms, bracelets, rings, earrings, necklaces, and pendants. The company operates through a network of 2,619 concept stores, which include 1,423 company owned stores, 700 franchise owned stores, and 496 third party distribution; and 4,154 other points of sale, as well as eSTOREs. Pandora A/S was founded in 1982 and is headquartered in Copenhagen, Denmark.
